The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in detecting and countering social bots on social media platforms. This topic falls under several sub-categories of computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), cybercrime (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SD), and computation and language (cs.CL). The paper covers aspects of all these sub-categories, but the focus on social media and bot detection makes cs.SI the most likely category.
